ia of Project Engineer I and Project Engineer II.\n\nManages subcontractors, tracks subcontractor progress and approves payment for services rendered in a timely and orderly manner.\n\nCorresponds with client to resolve payment on outstanding change orders. The determination of when to pursue payment is made with the Project Manager or other supervisor and is based on relationship, scale, and necessity.\n\nWrites formal letters as necessary to protect the company's interests and facilitate timely construction of the project.\n\nPrepares monthly progress billings and subcontractor payments with the intent of expediting payment from Owner.\n\nParticipates in subcontract negotiations and subcontract preparation. Works directly with subcontractors and monitors subcontractor pay estimates/submittals. Coordinates subcontractor meetings, as required.\n\nEstimates, prepares and submits Change Order requests to Owner and negotiates Change Orders with Owner, including all costs associated with change including, direct labor costs; equipment costs; material costs; subcontract costs; and project overhead costs. Maintains current Change Order Log and follows up with Owner on approvals.\n\nAuthorized to accept subcontractor work.\n\nResponsible for conforming the estimate to create the project budget.\n\nExpertly performs the duties of Project Engineer I and Project Engineer II\n\nUnderstands and upholds the terms and conditions of union master agreements for all trades.\n\nAssumes a leadership role with managing subcontractors and suppliers assuring contractual obligations are met by all parties.\n\nResponsible for successful and safe execution of the work.\n\nFinalizes shoring, framework and traffic control plans. Secures necessary approvals and communicates completed designs to Project Manager.\n\nOversees the implementation of adequate safety plans, safety meetings, method statements and safe working practices, as required by the Company and state and federal agencies.\n\nCreates and maintains project CPM schedule and other near term schedules.\n\nPrepares subcontract change orders for the approval of the Project Manager or other Supervisor.\n\nEstablishes and maintains strong working relationships with owners, agencies, subcontractors, inspectors, etc. providing customer service when necessary.\n\nProactively interacts with the Estimating staff ensuring consistent communication regarding pre-bid assistance, job status updates, changes to scope of work, owner/customer interactions, etc.\n\nPrepares periodic percent complete summaries.\n\nReviews vendor/supplier quotations with Project Estimator. Orders contract materials in a timely manner, coordinates material delivery schedules.\n\nRequired Skills / Technical Knowledge:\nBachelor's Degree (four year college or technical school)\n\n8-13 years of experience in Construction Engineering\n\nMust have computer experience using HCSS Heavy Job, Microsoft Word, Excel and Project. Vista Software is a plus.\n\nValid Driver's License with clean driver's abstract\n\nObtains and maintains CPR, AED and First Aid certification, OSHA 30, MUTCD Supervisor\n\nOther Requirements:\nMust have excellent communication skills to effectively work with customers, employees, management, vendors, utility companies and local state and federal agencies.\n\nMust have excellent negotiation skills.\n\nMust be proficient with surveying practices and use of equipment.\n\nMust be able to comprehend and follow occupational safety and health regulations, other state and federal regulations governing the construction industry, and Company practices and procedures.\n\nMust be able to accurately read blue prints, plans, specifications, contracts, bids, proposals and other construction documentation.\n\nMust understand the bidding process.\n\nMust understand drafting.\n\nMust be able to comprehend complex math concepts including geometry, algebra and trigonometry to measure calculate and forecast.\n\nUnderstand different signa